            <title>[QPIDJMS-335] SCRAM-SHA mechanism impls erroneously escape &quot;=&quot; and &quot;,&quot; in the password during processing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-335</link>
                <project id="12314524" key="QPIDJMS">Qpid JMS</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Per discussion on &lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/qpid-users/201710.mbox/%3C1507290028737-0.post%40n2.nabble.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/qpid-users/201710.mbox/%3C1507290028737-0.post%40n2.nabble.com%3E&lt;/a&gt; the client is erroneously escaping &quot;=&quot; and &quot;,&quot; during password handling, whereas the SCRAM mechanisms only require this for the username and some other cases, causing authentication to fail when they are present as the wrong value is used to compute the details sent to the server.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
